The article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama for Earth Day 2016. It discusses the importance of Earth Day and the need for collective action to combat climate change. The proclamation highlights the Paris Agreement, which aims to reduce global carbon pollution and limit global warming. It also emphasizes the role of American leadership in the fight against climate change and the actions taken by the Obama administration to reduce carbon pollution and transition to clean energy. The proclamation calls on all Americans to participate in programs and activities that protect the environment and contribute to a sustainable future.